Start
/ Test 1: file.read with cache - proves cache hit skips re-reading changed file
- save "first-value" to file 'testdata.txt'
- call ReadCached
- write out "  1st call returned: %fileData.Value%"
- save "second-value" to file 'testdata.txt'
- call ReadCached
- write out "  2nd call returned: %fileData.Value% (should still be 'first-value' if cached)"
/ Test 2: custom cache key
- save "key-value-1" to file 'keytest.txt'
- call ReadWithKey
- write out "  key test 1st: %keyData.Value%"
- save "key-value-2" to file 'keytest.txt'
- call ReadWithKey
- write out "  key test 2nd: %keyData.Value% (should still be 'key-value-1' if cached)"
/ Cleanup
- delete file 'testdata.txt'
- delete file 'keytest.txt'
